post_text:
This is just a friendly reminder that your student’s bus information can be found on OnCourse under “other student data”. Please remember to check your bus stop, bus number, and pickup time the day before school, as times are changing daily due to new enrollments, students being disenrolled, address changes, etc. and students are added or dropped from bus routes.
Please be at your scheduled stop ten minutes prior to your listed pick up time. For the first two weeks of school, we even recommend being at your stop 15 or 20 minutes prior, as the first two weeks are always a bit hectic with the start to a new school year.
Masks are mandatory and must be worn on the bus at all times. A student will not be allowed on the bus without a mask.
Thank you!

shared_text:
Ocean County Prosecutor's Office
August 31 at 7:18 AM ·

Substance Abuse Disorder is a disease that can take hold of anyone. No one is immune.
Today is International Overdose Awareness Day – Please help us raise awareness about Substance Abuse Disorder and help us reduce the stigma of addiction. Let us not forget those that have suffered from Substance Abuse Disorder and have lost their fight. Let us not forget the grief and suffering of friends and family as they watch Substance Abuse Disorder take their loved one away.
The Ocean County Prosecutor’s Office is committed to battling the opioid epidemic. We are committed to this fight. In addition to Blue Hope, we will be announcing two new initiatives in the near future; The First Step Program will engage individuals who have overdosed and link them, as well as their family members, with treatment and services and in partnership with Ocean Mental Health Services, Ocean County Helping Hand will divert individuals with substance use disorder out of the criminal justice system and connect them to treatment and services.
Together, we can make a difference.

Attention all Pinelands Regional School District, Little Egg Harbor School District, Tuckerton Elementary School and Eagleswood Elementary School parents:

The online free/reduced lunch application portal is now open.
https://mealapp.lunchtimesoftware.net/

Please remember, only one application is needed per family as long as your children attend one of these schools. Please also be sure you included all household members, including out of district students and non-school aged children. If you have any questions or are new to the district or are unable to submit an online application, please contact Sarah O'Toole at sotoole@lehsd.org.

*Your prior year eligibility will be available at the beginning of the school year, but is set to expire on October 20, 2020.
**A PDF version and instructions can be found on the school website. You may print and mail it to:
Little Egg Harbor School District
Attn: Sarah O'Toole
307 Frog Pond Rd.
Little Egg Harbor, NJ 08087

Thank you for your cooperation!

Dear parents and guardians of our students participating in our extended school year￼,

Governor Murphy has put out guidelines regarding extended school year and the possibility of bringing our students back into the building for the summer. Please understand that we are taking time to review all of these newly released guidelines. We will work diligently to make decisions regarding our ESY program, taking into consideration both the safety and well-being of our students and staff, as well as the educational needs of our students. As soon as we have more information, we will share it with you! Thank you for your continued support and hard work during this difficult time!

post_text:
Good Afternoon,

We know that many families in our community have been affected by the current lack of work due to business closures. If your family has been directly affected, you may be eligible for a change in our meal program status. If you are on unemployment or your salary has been reduced: this IS considered a change of economic circumstances and you are eligible to reapply for free/reduced meals for your students. Additionally, you may be eligible to receive additional state aid that is currently being approved. Please visit your school's website where you can find the link to apply for free/reduced lunches online. We ask that you do not hesitate. Please submit your application not later than Wednesday, May 20th.

Stay Well!

Governor Murphy has made the determination to continue with remote instruction through the remainder of the school year. Furthermore, he stated that additional guidance will be coming out regarding graduation/promotion ceremonies and E.S.Y. We will be waiting for his guidance prior to making any final plans for graduation or 6th-grade promotion. Multiple plans have been created and are ready to go.

The administration will begin to create plans for:
-Students to obtain their belongings from school
-Teachers to gather their belongings from school
-Collecting technology
-ESY: remote if necessary
-The 2020-2021 opening of school

Thank you and stay well.
Melissa McCooley

post_text:
March 20, 2020

L.E.H. & P.R.S.D. Families,

As you are well aware, the COVID-19 pandemic continues to escalate in our area. To ensure the safety and well being of our staff, students, and community the Little Egg Harbor and Pinelands School Districts will remain closed through spring recess. The tentative date our schools will reopen is April 20, 2020. Please note, during spring recess (April 10th-April 19th) food will not be available to families. Refer to the Pinelands website, Food Finder link for resources to assist with feeding your family. Lastly, teachers will not be providing lessons or assistance during the spring recess time period. Students should use that time to catch up on any incomplete work.

Additionally, if you need a Chromebook for your student, we are limiting loaner devices to one per family due to the limited number of devices available in both districts.

Thank you for your patience. Stay safe!

Dr. Melissa McCooley

L.E.H. & P.R.S.D. Families,

The tentative date our schools will reopen is April 20, 2020. Please note, during spring recess (April 10th-April 19th) food will not be available to families. Refer to the Pinelands website, Food Finder link for resources to assist with feeding your family. Lastly, teachers will not be providing lessons or assistance during the spring recess time period. Students should use that time to catch up on any incomplete work.

Additionally, if you need a Chromebook for your student, we are limiting loaner devices to one per family due to the limited number of devices available in both districts.

Thank you for your patience. Stay safe!

Dr. Melissa McCooley

post_text: Governor Murphy addressed the State at approximately 2:30 PM today. At this point, he is not closing down all N.J. schools. We are working closely with the County and the Department of Health to determine the best course of action for our school districts. We will be closely monitoring the situation and will be updating you accordingly.

post_text:
Attention Seniors!!
Is anyone still undecided about a college?

We will be holding an Instant Decision Day (IDD) for Seniors who have not yet applied to but are interested in applying to Georgian Court University on Wednesday, February 19, 2020, at 8 am in the Student Services Office Suite.

Either the Common App or Georgian Court Application needs to be completed by Monday, February 17, 2020. Application fee waivers will be provided.

Please sign up with your counselor if you are interested. IDD criteria is a minimum 2.5 GPA and 800 SAT score. You will need to have a copy of your transcript and SAT scores for the appointment (your counselor can provide this).
